.TH "init_statfs" 9 "init_statfs" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
init_statfs \- look up and initialize master and local (per node) statfs inodes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" init_statfs
.BI "(struct gfs2_sbd *sdp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sdp" 12
The GFS2 superblock
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This should be called after the jindex is initialized in \fBinit_journal\fP and
before \fBgfs2_journal_recovery\fP is called because we need to be able to write
to these inodes during recovery.
.SH "RETURN"
errno
